\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. G. elatum} (Fischer ex Sprengel) Boiss. in DC.,{\i  Prodr.}{\b  12:} 634 (1848). Plant 30-80 cm, sparsely pubescent. Leaves 6-15 × 2·5-4 cm, obovate to oblanceolate, obtuse or emarginate, mucronate. Spikes 1·5-2·5 cm; spikelets 2- to 3(4)-flowered, scarcely contiguous. Bracts c. 4 mm, entire, with wide, hyaline margin. Calyx 5-6·5 mm; tube hairy, twice as long as the limb. •{\i  S.E. Russia, W. Kazakhstan}. Rs (C, E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. G. speciosum} (L.) Boiss.,{\i  loc. cit. }(1848). Stems 10-50 cm, stout, subangular. Leaves 3-8 × 1-3 cm, obovate to obcuneate, obtuse, mucronate. Scales 1-2 cm. Spikes 1-2 cm, globose dense; spikelets 3- to 4-flowered. Inner bract 2-fid, rarely entire, outer bract 7-8 mm, usually puberulent, with wide, hyaline margin. Calyx 7-8 mm; lobes wider than long, or obscure. Corolla reddish-purple.{\i  E. Russia, from c.} 51°{\i  to} 57°{\i  N}. Rs (C, E). ({\i N. & C. Asia}.)
\par

