\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. G. heldreichii} Halacsy, {\i Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien }{\b 36:} 241 (1886). Plant 10-20 cm, glabrous; stems slender, cylindrical, flexuous, rough. Leaves 5-6 × c. 1·5 cm, spathulate, whitish-punctate. Scales c. 4 mm; mucro 2-3 mm. Spikes 2-3 cm, lax, with 3 spikelets per cm; spikelets usually 1-flowered. Bracts glabrous; inner bract 3·5-4 mm, 3-fid; outer bract c. 2 mm, acuminate. Calyx 6·5 mm; tube pubescent, 4 times as long as the limb; lobes longer than wide. Corolla whitish. •{\i  E. Greece} ({\i Thessalia}). Gr.
